The idea came out of a research project by co-founder Dino DiStefano, who with two colleagues developed "Infer", a program which could point to critical flaws such as "memory leaks" - which can make programs and computer crash - or conversely show that software was fine. Overall, 90% of crashes are caused by a single type of error.
